The paper deals with image smoothing, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The proposed benchmark includes a dataset with groundtruth image smoothing results and baseline algorithms built upon deep convolutional network architectures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with visual object categories, loss functions, and deep networks, which are also relevant to the Graphics (cs.GR), Multimedia (cs.MM), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
